- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the state complexity of automata recognizing a language related to the Thue-Morse set.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also likely as the paper involves combinatorial and number-theoretic arguments.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with the expansion of integers in a given base.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper involves constructing and analyzing automata.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also less likely but possible as the paper deals with the complexity of recognizing a language.
